  "text": "We recently reported that YY1 depletion reduced both proliferation and xenograft tumor growth of breast cancer cells . To evaluate whether YY1 associates with clinical outcomes, we analyzed a gene array dataset consisting of samples from 258 breast cancer patients [CITATION_1] . YY1 levels of all samples and three top YY1 expression tiles (50th%, 25th%, and 10th%) correlated monotonically with the decreasing distant metastasis-free survival (DMFS) of the patients ( Figure 1A) , suggesting the potential of YY1 as a prognostic marker for breast cancer patients.",
